Steps.Message: Update at 22:27 - Thanks for your continued patience over tonight. Our staff have now restored power to all but five properties, so if your power is on now, send CANCEL to 80876 to stop SMS updates. Otherwise, in order to get the last if the power on safely, we need to connect a temporary generator, as this is the fastest and safest course. Based on how long our staff think it will take to deliver, site and connect the generator, we're now hoping to have the last of the power restored by 01:00-02:00. We're sorry to advise another delay, but we'll continue to keep you updated with progress.

We became aware of this power cut at 17:33. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing
